WEBVTT

00:10.760 --> 00:11.886
Sorry.

00:13.388 --> 00:14.222
Who are you?

00:15.390 --> 00:17.976
I’m the sorcerer who set up this barrier.

00:18.643 --> 00:20.437
This place was chosen

00:21.271 --> 00:23.148
for a killing game.

00:23.857 --> 00:27.776
Unfortunately, it’s not exactly an honor.

00:27.777 --> 00:29.320
A killing game…

00:31.072 --> 00:33.992
Could you not do that at my place?

00:37.078 --> 00:38.830
You’re funny.

00:39.539 --> 00:43.333
There’s an old execution ground
a short distance from here.

00:43.334 --> 00:45.878
That’s the center of the barrier.

00:45.879 --> 00:48.047
It’s about a five to six kilometer radius.

00:48.965 --> 00:52.134
I pushed things to the limit
to create this barrier,

00:52.135 --> 00:55.221
so I can’t impose
overly unreasonable conditions.

00:55.805 --> 00:58.807
Those of you who were inside it
from the start

00:58.808 --> 01:00.935
have the right to leave.

01:01.978 --> 01:03.271
Just once.

01:04.230 --> 01:07.984
If you want, when you wake up,
you’ll be outside the barrier.

01:10.111 --> 01:11.237
So, what’ll it be?

01:11.780 --> 01:13.698
When I wake up?

01:15.700 --> 01:17.160
Is this a dream?

01:17.744 --> 01:21.331
A gap between dream and reality.
Like a curse.

01:26.753 --> 01:29.880
Be careful. Take it slow.

01:29.881 --> 01:32.884
There are already some eager ones outside.

02:00.453 --> 02:03.873
Oh, right. I almost forgot.

02:05.458 --> 02:08.461
Thanks for being nice to my son.

02:11.339 --> 02:12.464
<i>Sasaki!</i>

02:12.465 --> 02:14.008
Sasaki!

02:16.761 --> 02:17.886
Iguchi!

02:17.887 --> 02:20.890
Thank God, there’s someone I know!

02:21.474 --> 02:23.183
MY FEET ACHE
I DON'T HAVE MY GLASSES

02:23.184 --> 02:24.226
IGUCHI

02:24.227 --> 02:26.478
Where are we?

02:26.479 --> 02:29.274
Somewhere between Kotodai
and Hirose Dori, I think.

02:29.858 --> 02:30.984
More importantly, look.

02:31.609 --> 02:34.779
As an Occult Club member,
what do you make of this?

02:35.738 --> 02:38.157
What do you mean?

02:38.158 --> 02:41.452
NOVEMBER 1ST 6:02 A.M., SENDAI BARRIER

02:42.954 --> 02:44.539
Can I talk about a dream I had?

02:45.415 --> 02:48.668
Everyone is doing that.
A long-haired guy in a robe, right?

02:49.502 --> 02:52.838
So you saw him too?
About his son and all that…

02:52.839 --> 02:55.383
What? No, that part’s new to me.

02:59.888 --> 03:00.889
Itadori?

04:34.941 --> 04:38.443
Seriously? Mr. Gojo was sealed?

04:38.444 --> 04:39.862
- Seriously.
- Seriously.

04:42.740 --> 04:44.449
What?

04:44.450 --> 04:48.204
Also, sorry to pile this on,
but the principal is dead.

04:53.167 --> 04:54.751
Panda?

04:54.752 --> 04:56.878
Sorry. I kept quiet.

04:56.879 --> 04:57.880
But it’s true.

04:58.756 --> 05:02.301
It’s okay, Itadori. Not in Shibuya.

05:02.302 --> 05:04.387
After that,
things got messy with the higher-ups.

05:05.221 --> 05:07.639
That doesn’t make it okay.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.975
The principal was your…

05:09.976 --> 05:14.022
I know, and I said it’s okay. Thanks.

05:14.939 --> 05:18.817
If you’re saying that,
we can’t say anything.

05:18.818 --> 05:19.861
Yes.

05:20.695 --> 05:24.614
Still, everyone who helped me ends up…

05:24.615 --> 05:25.991
I haven’t felt this down

05:25.992 --> 05:29.578
since Yakul got an arrow in the butt.

05:29.579 --> 05:31.872
You’ve lived one hell of a life…

05:31.873 --> 05:33.373
Fine.

05:33.374 --> 05:36.044
I’ll help settle the Culling Game.

05:38.713 --> 05:40.423
Don’t get it twisted.

05:41.215 --> 05:45.136
I’m not doing this out of kindness.
This is a deal.

05:45.678 --> 05:51.391
You got it? Once the Culling Game is over,
you guys will help me.

05:51.392 --> 05:56.271
You want a say in revising
the jujutsu regulations, right?

05:56.272 --> 05:59.483
Now that curses are public knowledge,

05:59.484 --> 06:02.986
a revision is inevitable.

06:02.987 --> 06:05.114
But what exactly are you going to do?

06:06.491 --> 06:09.701
Either way, I don’t think
it will be that hard.

06:09.702 --> 06:14.624
What? What do you know, sea urchin?

06:15.500 --> 06:18.002
I’m head of the Zen'in clan.

06:21.297 --> 06:22.632
- Really?
- What?

06:25.051 --> 06:27.844
<i>What? No way!</i>

06:27.845 --> 06:31.431
<i>Sorry, but that’s the biggest shock
I’ve had all day.</i>

06:31.432 --> 06:36.311
<i>If one of the Big Three backs me,
getting a say in the revision is easy.</i>

06:36.312 --> 06:37.729
<i>The problem is what comes after.</i>

06:37.730 --> 06:41.818
<i>How do we keep the Zen'in clan
out of running the fight club?</i>

06:42.860 --> 06:45.570
- Sea urchin head!
- It’s Fushiguro.

06:45.571 --> 06:46.614
Fushiguro, my boy!

06:51.285 --> 06:53.161
Let’s be friends.

06:53.162 --> 06:54.329
Okay.

06:54.330 --> 06:56.581
THE ZEN'IN FAMILY
WAS ANNIHILATED THE NEXT DAY

06:56.582 --> 07:00.794
All right. Next is assigning
which colony barriers we head to.

07:00.795 --> 07:02.379
Yuta was in Miyagi, right?

07:02.380 --> 07:06.049
Ring-ring!

07:06.050 --> 07:09.219
A rule has been added to the Culling Game

07:09.220 --> 07:11.388
by a player!

07:11.389 --> 07:13.849
Rule nine.
Players may view other players’ info.

07:13.850 --> 07:16.643
<i>Their name, points,</i>

07:16.644 --> 07:18.145
<i>number of rules they have added,</i>

07:18.146 --> 07:21.274
<i>and which colony barrier they’re in.</i>

07:22.358 --> 07:23.400
I’m Kogane!

07:23.401 --> 07:26.779
I’m the liaison
between players and the Culling Game!

07:27.363 --> 07:29.614
Did it just switch personalities
halfway through?

07:29.615 --> 07:32.784
The first one was an announcement
from the Culling Game!

07:32.785 --> 07:37.372
This one is me as the liaison

07:37.373 --> 07:38.833
attached to player Yuji Itadori.

07:40.585 --> 07:43.253
Oh, right, that’s what Tengen said…

07:43.254 --> 07:45.046
No, that’s not right.

07:45.047 --> 07:48.216
Why is Itadori already counted
as a player?

07:48.217 --> 07:51.970
You need to have received techniques
or cursed objects from Kenjaku,

07:51.971 --> 07:55.558
and then enter a colony barrier
to become a player, right?

07:56.225 --> 07:58.602
<i>Someone like Yuji Itadori,</i>

07:58.603 --> 08:00.854
<i>who ingested a cursed object I gave out…</i>

08:00.855 --> 08:04.232
<i>A thousand years ago, I didn’t
only make contracts with sorcerers…</i>

08:04.233 --> 08:06.902
<i>He was a real person.</i>

08:06.903 --> 08:09.154
<i>From over 1,000 years ago, though.</i>

08:09.155 --> 08:11.324
- Sukuna…
- Sukuna?

08:11.991 --> 08:14.034
Maybe Sukuna was one of the sorcerers

08:14.035 --> 08:16.496
who made a contract with Kenjaku
and became a cursed object?

08:17.497 --> 08:21.124
<i>So joining the Culling Game
was part of that contract?</i>

08:21.125 --> 08:22.793
Still, it’s weird.

08:23.294 --> 08:25.879
<i>You chose to ingest Sukuna’s finger.</i>

08:25.880 --> 08:26.964
I’m your witness.

08:31.135 --> 08:32.386
Let’s leave it for now.

08:32.970 --> 08:37.058
Itadori, have Kogane show us
the players’ information.

08:38.559 --> 08:40.602
Kogane. Can you do it?

08:40.603 --> 08:44.606
Sure can!

08:44.607 --> 08:45.441
PLAYER LIST

08:47.068 --> 08:48.194
This is him.

08:48.986 --> 08:51.113
He already has 200 points?

08:52.114 --> 08:54.449
Why do you think he added this rule?

08:54.450 --> 08:58.787
At the very least,
it means he has killed 40 people.

08:58.788 --> 09:01.081
Can't imagine he has an altruistic reason.

09:01.082 --> 09:02.832
But with this,

09:02.833 --> 09:07.379
we might be able to proceed
without killing anyone.

09:07.380 --> 09:11.633
Kogane. Can you list only the players
with 100 points or more?

09:11.634 --> 09:15.887
Well, I’m attached to Yuji Itadori.

09:15.888 --> 09:19.266
It’s fine. Just do what Fushiguro says.

09:19.267 --> 09:21.268
SEARCHING

09:21.269 --> 09:24.354
People dragged into this, like Tsumiki,

09:24.355 --> 09:26.982
won’t rush to leave the barrier
unless they panic.

09:26.983 --> 09:29.067
And incarnated sorcerers from the past

09:29.068 --> 09:32.362
all had their own reasons
for making contracts with Kenjaku.

09:32.363 --> 09:35.116
They’re not all highly-motivated.

09:35.700 --> 09:39.744
If there are still guys like Kashimo
who have points to spare…

09:39.745 --> 09:42.706
Right. Someone with 100 points or more

09:42.707 --> 09:46.293
who doesn’t plan to add a rule.
We’ll beat them…

09:46.294 --> 09:50.005
And make them create a way out
for Tsumiki!

09:50.006 --> 09:51.006
There it is.

09:51.007 --> 09:53.174
SEARCHING

09:53.175 --> 09:54.302
One more!

09:54.885 --> 09:56.428
- Yes!
- Yes!

09:56.429 --> 09:59.307
- First, we exploit Rule Eight.
- What?

09:59.932 --> 10:02.143
What was Rule Eight again?

10:02.810 --> 10:05.729
<i>If your points don’t change
within 19 days,</i>

10:05.730 --> 10:09.649
<i>your technique is confiscated and you die.</i>

10:09.650 --> 10:12.319
<i>So we add a rule stating</i>

10:12.320 --> 10:14.946
<i>"Allow players
to transfer points between themselves."</i>

10:14.947 --> 10:15.864
THIRD DAY-7:05 A.M-FIFTH DAY-09:58 A.M.
FIRST DAY-4:46 A.M.- 0:00

10:15.865 --> 10:18.742
<i>If we keep circulating points
among ourselves,</i>

10:18.743 --> 10:21.787
<i>we won’t have our techniques confiscated,
and won't die.</i>

10:22.413 --> 10:23.789
If possible, we add one more rule.

10:24.373 --> 10:25.915
<i>"You can spend points</i>

10:25.916 --> 10:29.294
<i>to withdraw from the Culling Game."</i>

10:29.295 --> 10:33.882
Wouldn’t that count as "a rule
that threatens to end the game"?

10:33.883 --> 10:35.675
I think so too.

10:35.676 --> 10:38.887
But if we include a condition
to pull a non-player into the Game

10:38.888 --> 10:41.848
as a substitute, it might work.

10:41.849 --> 10:43.725
Makes sense.

10:43.726 --> 10:46.102
Does Kogane decide details like that?

10:46.103 --> 10:49.272
Either way, we know what we have to do.

10:49.273 --> 10:53.944
Yeah. While we search for Angel,
who can break the Prison Realm’s seal…

10:55.029 --> 10:56.947
We’ll hunt Hajime Kashimo

10:57.782 --> 11:00.492
and Hiromi Higuruma.

11:00.493 --> 11:01.076
CONVINCING A PLAYER WITH 100 POINTS
WHO DOESN’T WANT TO ADD ANY NEW RULES

11:01.077 --> 11:01.660
HUNT HAJIME KASHIMO, HUNT HIROMI HIGURUMA

11:01.661 --> 11:02.911
TANINAKA GAINED 500 POINTS
OBITA GAINED 0 POINTS

11:02.912 --> 11:04.454
BARRIER-TOKYO NUMBER TWO

11:04.455 --> 11:06.916
No luck finding Angel.

11:07.583 --> 11:11.420
It’s probably not their real name.
Like you and Sukuna.

11:12.922 --> 11:15.882
Tengen said they’re on Tokyo’s east side…

11:15.883 --> 11:18.802
In the Tokyo 2 colony.

11:18.803 --> 11:20.721
Do we know what they look like?

11:21.347 --> 11:22.931
Seems you’ll know when you see them.

11:22.932 --> 11:25.850
- That doesn’t sound reassuring.
- What…

11:25.851 --> 11:29.187
Whatever. Panda and I will go to Tokyo 2.

11:29.188 --> 11:31.856
Fushiguro and Itadori will go to Tokyo 1.

11:31.857 --> 11:33.858
Kirara waits outside the barriers.

11:33.859 --> 11:34.776
What?

11:34.777 --> 11:35.653
We good?

11:36.278 --> 11:37.195
Based on what?

11:37.196 --> 11:41.825
Going by points, Kashimo is the strongest,
so it makes sense for me to take him on.

11:41.826 --> 11:43.952
So I’m left out?

11:43.953 --> 11:48.289
Panda has a good nose,
so focus on finding Angel.

11:48.290 --> 11:50.667
Okkotsu hasn’t contacted us,

11:50.668 --> 11:53.711
so phones probably don’t work
inside the barriers.

11:53.712 --> 11:57.132
We need someone outside
who can keep tabs on things.

11:57.133 --> 11:58.299
Okay…

11:58.300 --> 11:59.968
Wait.

11:59.969 --> 12:03.096
Maybe Fushiguro and I should split up.
If Sukuna--

12:03.097 --> 12:04.556
Shut up.

12:04.557 --> 12:06.015
Shut up?

12:06.016 --> 12:09.102
We can’t change the seniors’ roles.

12:09.103 --> 12:10.437
Stop being selfish.

12:10.438 --> 12:11.397
Selfish?

12:12.022 --> 12:13.982
I’m worried about you!

12:13.983 --> 12:16.901
You’re going to say that
every single time?

12:16.902 --> 12:19.529
What a pain. You’re wasting time.

12:19.530 --> 12:20.697
- What?
- What?

12:20.698 --> 12:21.823
Stop fighting.

12:21.824 --> 12:23.533
NOVEMBER 12TH, 12:00 P.M. TOKYO
7 DAYS 12 HOURS UNTIL TSUMIKI'S DEADLINE.

12:23.534 --> 12:25.827
<i>Yo. I’m Kogane.</i>

12:25.828 --> 12:28.288
<i>Inside this barrier, a killing game,</i>

12:28.289 --> 12:31.583
<i>the Culling Game is underway!</i>

12:31.584 --> 12:35.420
<i>Once you step inside, you’re a player too!</i>

12:35.421 --> 12:38.715
<i>Are you still going in?</i>

12:38.716 --> 12:39.966
- Yes.
- Yes.

12:39.967 --> 12:41.218
No problem.

12:45.055 --> 12:46.932
<i>Hey, Amai!</i>

12:49.310 --> 12:51.520
<i>I’ve been waiting
for your signal this whole time.</i>

12:52.104 --> 12:53.605
Well…

12:53.606 --> 12:55.899
Even if you say that,

12:55.900 --> 12:58.359
I can’t do anything
unless someone shows up…

12:58.360 --> 12:59.487
<i>What?</i>

13:00.529 --> 13:01.489
What's with you?

13:02.239 --> 13:03.240
You talking back at me?

13:04.783 --> 13:07.035
No, I… Sorry!

13:07.036 --> 13:08.662
<i>I’m begging you…</i>

13:09.580 --> 13:10.831
If you keep that up,

13:13.083 --> 13:14.710
I’ll run you over.

13:16.128 --> 13:18.546
We need to watch out
for incarnated sorcerers from the past.

13:18.547 --> 13:20.840
Yes, that’s what I figured.

13:20.841 --> 13:23.802
Explain it for me, Fushiguro.

13:24.762 --> 13:27.263
Some of them are from 1,000 years ago.

13:27.264 --> 13:30.975
The value of human life
was different even 100 or 200 years ago.

13:30.976 --> 13:32.519
And they’re sorcerers.

13:32.520 --> 13:36.606
<i>Back then, dying in battle was normal.
They want to die fighting.</i>

13:36.607 --> 13:39.777
<i>That might be why
they made a contract with Kenjaku.</i>

13:40.361 --> 13:44.113
Kashimo and Higuruma
are likely sorcerers from the past.

13:44.114 --> 13:45.907
Don’t expect to negotiate.

13:45.908 --> 13:48.827
And there are curses too.

13:49.411 --> 13:52.747
Especially at night.
If it’s a modern-day sorcerer

13:52.748 --> 13:55.041
who got dragged in like Tsumiki,

13:55.042 --> 13:58.087
we might be able
to exchange information with them.

14:00.339 --> 14:01.924
Yo, I’m Kogane!

14:02.633 --> 14:05.301
Inside this barrier, a killing game,

14:05.302 --> 14:08.137
the Culling Game is underway!

14:08.138 --> 14:11.558
Once you step inside, you’re a player too!

14:11.559 --> 14:14.018
Are you still going in?

14:14.019 --> 14:16.355
Yes. No problem.

14:18.274 --> 14:21.526
Megumi Fushiguro
has joined the Culling Game.

14:21.527 --> 14:23.570
Would you like to view the Rules?

14:23.571 --> 14:25.906
- No. I don’t need them.
- Huh?

14:26.490 --> 14:27.907
- Itadori.
- Yes?

14:27.908 --> 14:30.411
First, we gather info on Higuruma.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.621
- Let’s go.
- Okay!

14:38.335 --> 14:39.295
Fushiguro is gone!

14:40.004 --> 14:42.422
<i>When a player enters
a Culling Game barrier,</i>

14:42.423 --> 14:44.340
<i>they’re randomly transferred</i>

14:44.341 --> 14:49.095
<i>to one of nine preset locations.</i>

14:49.096 --> 14:54.017
<i>This is a phenomenon
not listed in the rules.</i>

14:54.018 --> 14:56.477
<i>At those nine locations, they’re waiting.</i>

14:56.478 --> 14:57.605
They’re here!

14:58.188 --> 15:02.943
<i>They target players
thrown off by the unexpected…</i>

15:12.077 --> 15:13.495
<i>Newbie hunters.</i>

15:15.372 --> 15:17.749
<i>This guy is tough!</i>

15:17.750 --> 15:19.876
<i>Most people get shredded up by this.</i>

15:19.877 --> 15:21.628
<i>Yet he’s still standing.</i>

15:21.629 --> 15:23.172
<i>He’s no ordinary guy.</i>

15:32.473 --> 15:35.434
Darling, let’s regroup…

15:38.896 --> 15:43.107
That was easy.
I need to ask about Higuruma.

15:43.108 --> 15:45.235
Then I have to find Fushiguro.

15:45.945 --> 15:47.404
What the hell?

15:48.072 --> 15:50.032
What did you do to my woman?

15:50.908 --> 15:52.451
I can ask him, then.

15:53.369 --> 15:57.121
Hababa is here. Did he take Hanyu out?

15:57.122 --> 15:59.625
<i>That guy… I’ve seen him somewhere…</i>

16:01.085 --> 16:02.168
Itadori!

16:02.169 --> 16:05.964
It hurts. It hurts so bad.

16:05.965 --> 16:09.050
Why would you do this to me?

16:09.051 --> 16:10.803
You attacked me first.

16:11.387 --> 16:14.431
<i>Damn! This split was unexpected.</i>

16:15.015 --> 16:16.100
Find something?

16:17.142 --> 16:19.227
<i>Nue couldn't find him either.</i>

16:19.228 --> 16:21.605
<i>This colony is way bigger than Shibuya.</i>

16:22.189 --> 16:24.316
<i>We’re probably more than
two kilometers apart…</i>

16:25.109 --> 16:26.819
<i>But our destination is set.</i>

16:28.070 --> 16:30.239
Do you know a sorcerer named Higuruma?

16:30.906 --> 16:34.659
Men really think that if they hit a woman,
she’ll do whatever they say.

16:34.660 --> 16:35.702
Answer me.

16:35.703 --> 16:37.954
Yes, I’m sorry.

16:37.955 --> 16:40.456
Higuruma… You mean that guy?

16:40.457 --> 16:41.959
He has 100 points.

16:42.710 --> 16:44.128
Do you know where he is?

16:47.047 --> 16:49.550
I see. So that’s what this is about.

17:02.730 --> 17:05.524
You brat!
How are you so physically powerful?

17:13.240 --> 17:15.826
<i>I thought being on lower ground
would be a problem,</i>

17:16.410 --> 17:18.912
<i>but his only way of attacking
is that propeller.</i>

17:38.974 --> 17:41.392
<i>To kill me, he has to get close.</i>

17:41.393 --> 17:43.062
<i>I’ll face him indoors.</i>

17:57.534 --> 17:59.411
I’ll turn you into a smoothie!

18:01.747 --> 18:04.583
<i>He's heading this way! Top of the head!</i>

18:06.960 --> 18:09.003
<i>That plane woman earlier</i>

18:09.004 --> 18:11.464
<i>had enough power to punch through
a building, with me in the way.</i>

18:11.465 --> 18:13.342
<i>But she went down from a throw like that.</i>

18:13.884 --> 18:17.512
<i>The farther they get
from the core of the cursed technique,</i>

18:17.513 --> 18:19.472
<i>the weaker they become.</i>

18:19.473 --> 18:23.684
<i>A binding vow? But no matter
how tough it is, a head is still a head.</i>

18:23.685 --> 18:27.439
<i>If I can land a hit, I can crack it open!</i>

18:39.326 --> 18:42.286
So you broke your fist?

18:42.287 --> 18:44.164
This fight is yours to lose!

18:52.881 --> 18:55.633
I didn’t break it. Ouch…

18:55.634 --> 18:58.219
I could tell you,

18:58.220 --> 19:00.556
but I want you to do something for me too.

19:02.641 --> 19:03.724
Say it.

19:03.725 --> 19:06.477
Say it? Please…

19:06.478 --> 19:08.772
- Tell me? Please…
- Say it.

19:10.232 --> 19:11.150
Okay.

19:12.901 --> 19:16.113
- Be my knight.
- Fine. That works.

19:18.532 --> 19:21.075
Am I really no fun to tease?

19:21.076 --> 19:24.954
We don’t have time. Hurry up. Walk…

19:24.955 --> 19:26.582
You do realize a knight

19:27.291 --> 19:30.836
risks their life to protect me, right?

19:32.004 --> 19:34.423
If what you’re saying is true…

19:36.508 --> 19:38.968
Hey, wake up.

19:38.969 --> 19:42.264
I want to ask about a sorcerer
named Higuruma…

19:42.806 --> 19:45.475
- Hey…
- Itadori…

19:47.186 --> 19:48.687
I know.

19:49.438 --> 19:51.231
I know about that Higuruma guy.

19:52.399 --> 19:53.233
If you’re lying,

19:55.027 --> 19:56.236
you know what happens, right?

19:56.737 --> 19:58.446
<i>I’m not like Itadori.</i>

19:58.447 --> 20:01.449
If I have to,
I can earn 100 points myself.

20:01.450 --> 20:03.826
Don’t call me "you."

20:03.827 --> 20:05.245
Call me Remi.

20:05.996 --> 20:08.332
Long time no see. Do you remember me?

20:09.666 --> 20:10.875
Who are you?

20:10.876 --> 20:13.044
<i>How does he know my name?</i>

20:13.045 --> 20:17.131
Sorry. It’s just that I know you.

20:17.132 --> 20:19.467
You’re famous.

20:19.468 --> 20:20.719
Nishinaka’s Tiger.

20:21.303 --> 20:23.679
Oh, so you’re from my hometown.

20:23.680 --> 20:25.139
EXCEPT BICYCLES

20:25.140 --> 20:28.559
So you aren't a sorcerer from the past?

20:28.560 --> 20:32.481
What? Do I really look
that old-fashioned to you?

20:33.065 --> 20:35.400
Why are you fighting so aggressively?

20:36.109 --> 20:37.110
Listen…

20:37.778 --> 20:39.737
Non-player civilians

20:39.738 --> 20:42.324
were let out of the colony barrier,
it seems,

20:42.824 --> 20:46.077
but for players who were already
inside the colony barrier…

20:46.078 --> 20:49.831
It has been 12 days
since the Culling Game started.

20:50.499 --> 20:53.417
I’m not doing this because I want to!

20:53.418 --> 20:55.379
If you don’t kill, you get killed!

20:57.005 --> 21:00.424
If you keep looking for a reason to fight,
you’ll be dead.

21:00.425 --> 21:03.053
After 12 days here,
you'll understand that.

21:03.720 --> 21:06.765
I’ve seen people get drunk with power too.

21:07.349 --> 21:10.602
So stop sorting people into
past sorcerer or modern sorcerer.

21:11.186 --> 21:13.479
<i>So past sorcerers are aggressive,</i>

21:13.480 --> 21:15.857
<i>and modern sorcerers
go into fight mode too.</i>

21:16.692 --> 21:19.151
<i>I said too much to Itadori…</i>

21:19.152 --> 21:22.990
Is that okay?
Weren’t those two your friends?

21:23.782 --> 21:27.994
I’m just an errand boy.
I would’ve been killed sooner or later.

21:27.995 --> 21:29.037
Wait.

21:29.955 --> 21:32.541
Tell me where you’re headed.

21:33.125 --> 21:38.463
Listen! If I tell you,
how do I know you won’t kill me after?

21:39.047 --> 21:40.965
I see… Well…

21:40.966 --> 21:43.218
I’m Amai. Rin Amai.

21:43.802 --> 21:46.137
What if you die before we get there?

21:46.138 --> 21:50.433
Come on! You'll protect me, right?

21:50.434 --> 21:52.018
And stop calling me "you"!

21:52.019 --> 21:53.019
Always a chance you'll die.

21:53.020 --> 21:56.230
Amai. Where’s Higuruma?

21:56.231 --> 21:59.608
Fine. I’ll give you a rough idea.

21:59.609 --> 22:02.653
Stronger ones gather in places
that used to be thriving.

22:02.654 --> 22:04.363
Supplies are plentiful there.

22:04.364 --> 22:06.449
- Higuruma is…
- Higuruma is

22:06.450 --> 22:07.867
- in Ikebukuro.
-…in Shinjuku.

22:07.868 --> 22:08.910
- There.
- There.

23:41.962 --> 23:45.464
<i>I simply see potential
in the Culling Game.</i>

23:45.465 --> 23:46.757
<i>Everyone in this country will die.</i>

23:46.758 --> 23:49.093
<i>You got played.</i>

23:49.094 --> 23:50.386
<i>Sorry, Itadori…</i>

23:50.387 --> 23:52.221
<i>A sorcerer connected to Kenjaku…</i>

23:52.222 --> 23:53.180
<i>I want to talk.</i>

23:53.181 --> 23:54.849
<i>Try again.</i>

23:54.850 --> 23:55.934
NEXT EPISODE
